reviewText: I haven't ordered this yet but will do I'm just wondering is this the last box set of naruto or is there more box sets coming out

A LOT happens in this set! This is a great set, a lot goes down and some major things are resolved. All episodes in this set are canon so no worries of filler. This set is really centered about the tailed beasts, so a lot is revealed about them. Naruto also gets a huge boost to battle against the tailed beasts and "Tobi", in his Kurama mode. Lastly, Sasuke enters the war and is able to reunite with Itachi to stop the reanimation jutsu. This here is when the war REALLY picks up and leads to even more exciting events to come.

Naruto Shippuden box set 26 continues the anime's Fourth Great Ninja War part 3 story arc that started on episode 321 in box set 25, with episode's 323-335. Just like the 25 dvd sets that have come before, this is once again a awesome set of episode's to add to your Naruto collection. Just like viz media always thanks it's fans for their support, it's been over 10 years since naruto came to the United States;  it's time for fans to say thank you Viz Media for supporting Naruto all these years. With many fantastic box set releases, and high quality English dub.

This is going to be a great volume. I was afraid they were going to end the DVD without concluding the Obito arc, but I guess they decided to extend it by a few episodes for this volume, which is great. My only complaint is that this is Obito's time in the spotlight, yet Madara is on the cover art. I don't like that decision, Obito should be on the cover.

This set has the incredible fight between Obito and Kakashi. The choreography, music, and animation of that fight places it in the top 5 of all Naruto battles. Also on this disc include the new generation of senin in combat together as well as the early stages of ten tail jinchuriki battle.

Incredible battle sequences, a lot of surprises. The five Kage finally come out to play a major role in a fight with the original Madarra and even though it is a sea saw battle, wow are there some surprises in this battle. The Allied ninja's have won on all fronts and now are racing to aid the five Kage in a show down of force. Toward the end we start to learn about Kabuto past for box set 27, where the first two episodes tell you things you probly never knew, like how Kabuto was secretly working for the foundation and how he met Orochimaru. But that is in the next set..  .
